history.content: You should be fine if you don't try to pile on another tech, but be prepared to work very hard. Both EE16b and CS70 have time consuming homeworks, and EE 16B also has labs which can take some time. best of luck.

children.subject: Dont rush, focus on declaring and push EECS16b to fall if u can, esp if u are on the border GPA

history.content:
Hi Everyone,

I'm a new Junior Transfer and I was planning on taking EECS 16B and CS70 together along with an American Cultures class, but not sure if this would be a good idea. I'm currently taking CS61B and EECS 16A, and I'm struggling with the first few circuits stuff. I'm a bit lost in the class and find the hw in 16A to be a lot time consuming(7-9 hrs). Declaring is my top most priority so I was just wondering is taking 16B and CS70 together along with any American Cultures class a good idea, or should I push EECS 16B to next Fall or push CS70 to summer? Also just in case if I was to push any class to later semesters, can anyone recommend me any easy Upper Division class I can take. Thanks in advance.
history.subject: EECS 16B and CS70 Together
